race.comment: MAXANDUS (2) was leading on the turn and fought on to finish third over 900m at Gunnedah at his latest appearance. Should be prominent from the outset. Best form puts him right in this. BYLONG (6) showed good early dash and raced on the speed last start before fading to finish twelfth over 1318m at Dubbo. Well placed and should be tough to rein in. BONOYSTER (4) was out of the money when resuming with a fading tenth over 900m at Muswellbrook. Finds a more suitable contest and can find winning form. FLAMBOYANT LAD (1) is back from a spell of four-and-a-half months and does go well when fresh, including a win to launch last campaign over 1312m at Geelong. Sure to make his presence felt from the good gate.
